line) 29th June Evening Shift Chemistry - Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers Question 100 English Explanation\">","marks":4,"negativeMarks":-1,"topic":"Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers"},{"id":"1ky7c6up1","questionNumber":3,"subject":"Chemistry","section":"A","questionType":"MCQM","questionText":"The reactivity of compound Z with different halogens under appropriate conditions is given below<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l1anz6zy/70f61afc-1874-4524-8e87-28bf8a750c02/7086edd0-ae8f-11ec-8c7e-1b4a74698496/file-1l1anz6zz.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l1anz6zy/70f61afc-1874-4524-8e87-28bf8a750c02/7086edd0-ae8f-11ec-8c7e-1b4a74698496/file-1l1anz6zz.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2014 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers Question 28 English\"><br>The observed pattern of electrophilic substitution can be explained by","options":["the steric effect on the halogen","the steric effect of the tert-butyl group","the electronic effect of the phenolic group","the electronic effect of the tert-butyl group"],"correctOption":0,"solution":"Steric effect of halogens are as follows Cl<sub>2</sub> &lt; Br<sub>2</sub> &lt; I<sub>2</sub><br><br>Electronic effect of phenolic group directs the approaching electrophile towards ortho and para positions. Tertiary butyl group has large size so it causes steric effect around aromatic nucleus. On the basis of above factors the products of the given reactions are as follows<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l1ao3gox/ce548717-dad3-4e52-8b09-5b33fef71b47/e740e930-ae8f-11ec-8c7e-1b4a74698496/file-1l1ao3goz.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l1ao3gox/ce548717-dad3-4e52-8b09-5b33fef71b47/e740e930-ae8f-11ec-8c7e-1b4a74698496/file-1l1ao3goz.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2014 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers Question 28 English Explanation\"><br>Hence, orientation in electrophilic substitution reaction is decided by<br><br>(a) The steric effect of the halogen<br><br>(b) The steric effect of the tert-butyl group<br><br>(c) The electronic effect of the phenolic group<br><br>So, (a), (b) and (c) are correct choices.","marks":3,"negativeMarks":-1,"topic":"Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers","correctOptionsArray":[0,1,2]},{"id":"5xZkfkGGE195L7RS","questionNumber":4,"subject":"Chemistry","section":"A","questionType":"MCQ","questionText":"The product of the reaction given below is : \n<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l7zdxc1s/31a7ba75-be88-4509-bced-5d3f27180f43/06076b10-32f1-11ed-8cf6-c1445513adbd/file-1l7zdxc1t.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l7zdxc1s/31a7ba75-be88-4509-bced-5d3f27180f43/06076b10-32f1-11ed-8cf6-c1445513adbd/file-1l7zdxc1t.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2016 (Offline) Chemistry - Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers Question 160 English\">","options":["<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l7zdyut1/880f2324-35ab-42ae-900c-57f79c41fb1c/3053aa50-32f1-11ed-8cf6-c1445513adbd/file-1l7zdyut2.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l7zdyut1/880f2324-35ab-42ae-900c-57f79c41fb1c/3053aa50-32f1-11ed-8cf6-c1445513adbd/file-1l7zdyut2.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2016 (Offline) Chemistry - Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers Question 160 English Option 1\">","<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l7zdzem9/f27e315e-0443-487d-a5db-c0cc790665b4/3fa18310-32f1-11ed-8cf6-c1445513adbd/file-1l7zdzema.png?format=png\" da